On the evening of January 25, 2025, after a family dinner, my father gifted me his cherished wooden toolbox, which he had kept for many years. The contents of the box included:  
1. Textbooks such as *Fundamentals of Electrical Engineering* and *Electric Motors and Drives* that he used in his youth, with detailed notes in the margins;  
2. A yellowed work notebook, documenting troubleshooting cases and practical mnemonics he had summarized over years of practice;  
3. A well-maintained set of old-fashioned electrical tools (screwdrivers, pliers, voltage testers, etc.).  
My father advised me to build a solid theoretical foundation, emphasizing that these practical tools and case notes are invaluable assets, representing the inheritance of experience. I will make good use of them to prepare for the Senior Technician certification exam.

I. Workload Observations:  
1. Frequent line faults occur due to summer thunderstorms;  
2. Increased emergency repair tasks often require temporary dispatch.  

II. Personal Condition:  
1. Increased pressure in handling sudden tasks, requiring constant readiness;  
2. High physical exertion when working in hot and humid environments.

I. Strengths: Extensive technical experience and strong problem-solving abilities;  
II. Weaknesses: Lack of market knowledge and limited resources;  
III. Family Situation: Stable but requires caution.  
IV. Assessment Conclusion: A systematic review of recent business ideas, combined with research and reflection, indicates high risks. At this stage, priority should be given to preparing for the senior technician certification, deepening technical expertise, and maintaining family stability, while other plans should be temporarily postponed.

Key Points from Today's Site Inspection:  
1. Three severely aged joints (locations marked in photos);  
2. Prominent issue of tangled wiring in the narrow stairwell;  
3. Discussed technical details with Team Leader Zhang and Engineer Chen;  
4. Provided an oral report to Director Wang on the preliminary plan and safety recommendations.  
A written report and preliminary budget must be completed within this week.
